        "mode": "full",
        "content": "# JPM \u2014 Technicals\n\n## TL;DR\n\nAs of the Apr 15 run, JPM was in the textbook \"buy-the-dip in an uptrend\" configuration: daily chart fully aligned bullish (EMAs stacked up, positive MACD, ADX confirming trend), while the hourly chart had been hammered to extreme oversold readings \u2014 RSI 31, stochastic near zero \u2014 on post-earnings intraday selling [run: 20260415_093758]. Seven of ten strategy models called bullish. By the Apr 17 run, the stock had moved up to ~$310 and the setup had evolved to trend continuation with split conviction (momentum ranker neutral, Druckenmiller bearish on fundamentals) [run: 20260417_233350].\n\n## Multi-timeframe state (as of Apr 15 run)\n\n| Timeframe | State | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Daily | Bullish trend | EMAs stacked up, MACD positive, ADX confirming [run: 20260415_093758] |\n| Hourly | Extreme oversold | RSI 31, stochastic ~0, multiple oversold indicators at extreme [run: 20260415_093758] |\n| Apr 17 daily | Bullish, less extreme | Trend intact but momentum ranker neutral, daily uptrend continued [run: 20260417_233350] |\n\n## Key levels (from Apr 15 run)\n\n| Level | Value | Source |\n|---|---|---|\n| Entry zone | ~$304\u2013$305 | Apr 15 decision entry $304.78 [run: 20260415_093758] |\n| Target | $319.60 | Apr 15 PM decision [run: 20260415_093758] |\n| Stop / invalidation | $298.30 | Below this level, buy thesis fails [run: 20260415_093758] |\n| Apr 17 entry | $309.95 | Subsequent run entry price [run: 20260417_233350] |\n| Apr 17 target | $325.00 | [run: 20260417_233350] |\n| Apr 17 stop | $304.00 | [run: 20260417_233350] |\n| Analyst consensus target | $337\u2013$345 | Median analyst cluster [run: 20260415_093758] |\n| High-end analyst target | $365 | Goldman Sachs post-Q1 raise [run: 20260415_093758] |\n\n## Setup type\n\n**Apr 15:** Classic post-earnings buy-the-dip. Daily uptrend intact after Q1 beat; intraday selling created hourly oversold extreme. Buy signal was timing-driven (mean revert hourly into daily trend), not breakout-driven. Risk/reward: 2.18:1 [run: 20260415_093758].\n\n**Apr 17:** Trend continuation. Stock moved up ~$5 from Apr 15 entry. Lower conviction than Apr 15 \u2014 Head Trader had mixed reads across strategies; momentum ranker neutral, Druckenmiller bearish on fundamentals. Risk/reward: 2.53:1 [run: 20260417_233350].\n\n**Apr 11 (pre-earnings):** Hold. Head Trader was 65% bullish but Q1 earnings binary risk the next trading day and R:R only 1.5:1 at $308 failed the 2:1 minimum [run: swing_20260411_211655].\n\n## Last updated\n\n2026-04-29. Technical reads from three runs: swing_20260411_211655 (hold, pre-earnings), 20260415_093758 (buy, post-earnings dip), 20260417_233350 (buy, trend continuation).\n",
